Description:
------------
The script "run.sh" creates the following private network:
1- Bind9 DNS caching server with one private zone. You can edit RESOURCE_NAME and ZONE_NAME in the vars file to change the zone name to something else.
    The default zone name is contoso.udc.
2- Nginx web server with a single html page. The web server also hosts a PAC script file.
3- Squid proxy server that blocks all destinations except for what's allowed.
    You can edit PROXY_ALLOWED_NAMES and PROXY_BYPASS_NAMES in the vars file to allow or deny other destinations.

Requirements:
-------------
1- Tunnel server installation
2- docker
3- jq

If you have a valid Tunnel server installation then all the above requirements are met and you can create the private net immediately.

How to use:
-----------
1- Copy the directory privatenet to the host of Tunnel Server.
2- To create the private network, on the Tunnel server run:
    # chmod +x *.sh
    # ./run.sh
3- The script will output private DNS server and proxy server information to configure Tunnel Server and VPN profiles.
4- When no longer needed, on the Tunnel server run:
    # ./clean.sh
5- You can edit any files under the remote directory privatenet and run ./run.sh again. Always clean before creating the network again.
